Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, to sharpish turn. Clay fine buff-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 87, 2. Name Aineas. From the same die as less well preserved pieces from Lindos and the Athenian Agora. The only known usage of this job description.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0767)
